# ⭐ What the Node Type Registry actually is  
Right now, your engine does this:

```js
if (node.type === "timer") { ... }
if (node.type === "portal") { ... }
if (node.type === "wordPuzzle") { ... }
if (node.type === "gem") { ... }
if (node.type === "puzzle") { ... }
```

This works…  
…but it **does not scale**.

A commercial engine needs:

```js
NODE_RENDERERS = {
  timer: renderTimer,
  portal: renderPortal,
  wordPuzzle: renderWordPuzzle,
  gem: renderGem,
  puzzle: renderPuzzle,
  default: renderDefault
}
```

Then:

```js
const renderer = NODE_RENDERERS[node.type] || NODE_RENDERERS.default
renderer(node)
```

This gives you:

- Infinite scalability  
- Zero duplication  
- Zero drift  
- Perfect isolation  
- Perfect testability  
- Perfect extensibility  

This is the backbone of every real game engine.

